00:10:10.620 --> 00:10:15.170
Until a few years ago no Senator would ever
dream of going to the floor

00:10:15.170 --> 00:10:17.360
to mention another Senator by name

00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:20.670
without first notifying that Senator in advance

00:10:20.670 --> 00:10:23.970
thus the notified senator had the opportunity
to sit on the floor

00:10:23.970 --> 00:10:26.810
the hear the other Senator take him to task

00:10:26.810 --> 00:10:28.570
and usually in the quite

00:10:28.570 --> 00:10:31.060
polite terms, the gentleman from Massachusetts,

00:10:31.060 --> 00:10:32.480
and the like

00:10:32.480 --> 00:10:35.510
without question the tone of the speeches
was much milder

00:10:35.510 --> 00:10:38.040
when you had to look the opposing Senator

00:10:38.040 --> 00:10:39.320
in the eye.

00:10:39.320 --> 00:10:43.980
I recall that just a few years ago a republican
Senator went to the floor to challenge and

00:10:43.980 --> 00:10:44.500
contradict

00:10:44.500 --> 00:10:46.260
one of Senator Bob Byrd’s statements

00:10:46.260 --> 00:10:47.430
and he mentioned

00:10:47.430 --> 00:10:50.290
Senator Byrd by name without first notifying

00:10:50.290 --> 00:10:54.310
