Senator

00:11:00.570 --> 00:11:05.240
for failing to notify in advance and by the end
of the episode the republican Senator was

00:11:05.240 --> 00:11:07.560
publicly apologizing to Senator Byrd

00:11:07.560 --> 00:11:11.010
and the substantive issue of disagreement
faded in the background

00:11:11.010 --> 00:11:13.110
well the issue a protocol breached took

00:11:13.110 --> 00:11:15.430
the center stage

00:11:15.430 --> 00:11:17.320
unfortunately for the senate however

00:11:17.320 --> 00:11:21.700
that sense of protocol is today honored more
often in the breach

00:11:21.700 --> 00:11:25.560
perhaps not as it relates to Senator Byrd
but certainly as it relates to the ninety

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:26.040
nine

00:11:26.040 --> 00:11:28.080
other members of the senate

00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:31.640
this aggressive and personal partisanship
was not as evident

00:11:31.640 --> 00:11:33.340
even ten years ago.

00:11:33.340 --> 00:11:38.610
