nineteen ninety four he asked Orrin Hatch

00:11:38.610 --> 00:11:42.780
certainly a fierce republican partisan, to come
to Massachusetts to campaign for him

00:11:42.780 --> 00:11:47.220
but Orrin was on the ranking member of the health
committee and I was the chairman and Orrin

00:11:47.220 --> 00:11:49.180
refused to come in to Massachusetts

00:11:49.180 --> 00:11:51.620
to campaign against me

00:11:51.620 --> 00:11:55.280
collegiality particularly on our committee

00:11:55.280 --> 00:11:56.810
trumped partisanship

00:11:56.810 --> 00:11:58.860
contrast that with what we see today

00:11:58.860 --> 00:12:03.100
in just this last month the senate majority
leader Bill Friske went to south Dakota

00:12:03.100 --> 00:12:06.240
to actively campaign against the minority
leader

00:12:06.240 --> 00:12:07.550
Tom Daschle

00:12:07.550 --> 00:12:11.390
that is a dramatic and unprecedented move that
certainly does nothing

00:12:11.390 --> 00:12:13.540
to advance the collegiality.

00:12:13.540 --> 00:12:18.620
for nearly the entire history of the senate
collegiality didn't stop at the party line

00:12:18.620 --> 00:12:20.609
but after some seat change

00:12:20.609 --> 00:12:24.289
you're beginning to see that collegiality
is going to join the ranks

00:12:24.289 --> 00:12:26.450
of hand written letters

00:12:26.450 --> 00:12:30.210
soon to be considered a quaint old-fashioned
custom

00:12:30.210 --> 00:12:34.960
this decrease in collegiality is not in
my judgment the result of having any particular

00:12:34.960 --> 00:12:35.550
party

00:12:35.550 --> 00:12:36.740
in control

00:12:36.740 --> 00:12:40.490
I think it is partly the result of twenty
four hour news cycles

00:12:40.490 --> 00:12:43.920
in which talk radio and TV personalities keep
ratings up

00:12:43.920 --> 00:12:47.350
by engaging in strident and aggressively personal
attacks

00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:48.810
on politicians

00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:51.059
and that tone then spreads to discourse

00:12:51.059 --> 00:12:52.520
on capitol hill

00:12:52.520 --> 00:12:55.150
I certainly know something

00:12:55.150 --> 00:12:57.800
about throwing a little partisan red meat

00:12:57.800 --> 00:13:00.880
but I'm talking about something different
from that

00:13:00.880 --> 00:13:03.470
it's more of a take-no-prisoners approach

00:13:03.470 --> 00:13:04.640
to government

00:13:04.640 --> 00:13:09.140
that I do not believe is in the best interest
of the American people

00:13:09.140 --> 00:13:13.300
another reason for the changed tone of the
senate I believe is that today many more members

00:13:13.300 --> 00:13:14.330
